Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,, Welcome to The Deep Dive. Today,\N we're getting into a really pivotal time in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.75,0:00:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,, West Roshi history. Often talked about,\N maybe often misunderstood too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.35,0:00:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,, Definitely. We're talking about King Jher is the first and Queen
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.24,0:00:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,, Alice and Targaryen. Their long reign. Right. And our mission for you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.08,0:00:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,, listening is to take these sources,\N you know,\N the chronicles,\N letters,\N bits of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.08,0:00:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,, history you've given us,\N and really pull out the key insights.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,, Yeah. The surprising stuff,\N maybe even some unsettling details that make this
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.00,0:00:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,, period so,\N so unique. We're focusing mainly on the years 55 A.C. to 58 A.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.64,0:00:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,, Roughly,\N though we'll glance a bit beyond that too. It's a mix,\N isn't it? Amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.67,0:00:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,, achievements,\N but also some deep personal tragedies,\N kings,\N queens,\N dragons,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.32,0:00:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,, darkness,\N all shaping the kingdom. Absolutely. Most people know Jher is the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.84,0:00:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,, conciliator,\N right? His reign gets called a golden age. And you can see why on the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.87,0:00:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,, surface. For sure,\N long stretches of peace,\N prosperity,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.35,0:00:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,, westeros,\N the population apparently doubled and King's landing quadrupled.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.07,0:01:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,, That's huge. Yeah. And things like grain,\N fish prices drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.64,0:01:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,, Trade was booming. Crafts were flourishing,\N you know,\N farriers,\N goldsmiths,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.23,0:01:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,, brewers. It paints a picture of,\N well,\N things being pretty good for a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.23,0:01:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,, people. Almost I did it,\N really. It does sound that way. But,\N you know,\N like
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.92,0:01:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,, Sept and Barth said,\N it's easy to mistake it for one long,\N green,\N and gentle
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.07,0:01:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,, summer. But that prosperity didn't just happen easily. And 55 A.C.,\N where we're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.76,0:01:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,, kicking off this deep dive,\N actually started under this grim shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.52,0:01:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,, The year of the stranger. Exactly. And Princess area and Beleri and the Black
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.92,0:01:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,, Dread were still just gone,\N vanished,\N which is a really odd start for a supposed
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.52,0:01:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,, golden age,\N isn't it? It really is. You've got this incredible success story
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.32,0:01:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,, building,\N but it's haunted right from the start by this huge,\N unresolved
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,, personal tragedy. How does that work? Yeah. How do you reconcile those?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.28,0:01:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,, And immediately,\N you see the impact on Queen Rina Targaryen,\N area's mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.60,0:01:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,, She was,\N well,\N just break completely understandable. She'd left court taking
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.28,0:02:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,, dream fire and was just criss-crossing westeros. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.79,0:02:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,, Searching. Old town,\N high garden,\N cray call,\N casterly rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.60,0:02:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,, Just tireless and fruitless,\N sadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.48,0:02:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,, And then there's that account of her confrontation with Lord Franklin
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.92,0:02:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,, Farman on Fair Isle. She basically landed dream fire there and didn't hold back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.87,0:02:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,, Warned him about Beleriand. And that really highlights a difference,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.87,0:02:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,, doesn't it? Between Rina's approach and Jehary's,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.04,0:02:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,, Sempton Barth had that insight about the dragons. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.84,0:02:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,, That Targaryen power was immense,\N but the threat of it,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.92,0:02:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,, that was most potent when it was unspoken. Jehary's got that subtlety. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.43,0:02:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,, Rina though,\N she was direct,\N even reportedly boasted about,\N you know,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.20,0:02:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,, feeding her last husband,\N her dragon was probably didn't win her many friends
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.52,0:02:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,, among the lords,\N even if Jehary's didn't exactly condemn her for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,, No. And after that,\N she kind of retreated,\N flew over lonely places,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.40,0:02:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,, still searching,\N maybe just grieving,\N hard to say for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.36,0:02:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,, So while Rina is searching the skies,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.56,0:03:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,, you've got this other audacious thing happening across the narrow sea,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.96,0:03:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,, Alyssa Farman. Ah,\N yes,\N calling herself Alice Westhold by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.80,0:03:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,, And using those dragon eggs,\N she stole the ones Rina interested to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.96,0:03:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,, Exactly. Using them to fund building this ship,\N the sun chaser in bravos.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.00,0:03:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,, And this wasn't just any ship. No,\N a four-masted carrot built for long
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.24,0:03:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,, voyages,\N deep waters. She was planning something big.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,, People asked if she was sailing to ET and she apparently just laughed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.56,0:03:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,, so she was going much further. Yeah. Beyond the sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.48,0:03:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,, It's a fascinating clash of visions there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.56,0:03:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,, You have the maesters still kind of debating the edges of the known world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.68,0:03:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,, And Alyssa Farman is just convinced the world is far larger and far stranger than the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.92,0:03:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,, maesters imagine. She wasn't just looking for trade routes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.00,0:03:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,, No,\N she was looking for a whole new condense,\N wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.47,0:03:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,, Another SOS,\N another Sothorios,\N another Westeros.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.75,0:03:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,, It's incredibly bold,\N especially when you think about past failures like brand
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.15,0:03:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,, and the ship right,\N sailing north and vanishing. True.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.31,0:04:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,, But Alyssa heading south,\N paying triple wages,\N getting those high tower grandson's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.12,0:04:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,, on board. She had serious conviction and a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.15,0:04:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,, So back in King's Landing,\N well,\N all this is going on the searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.47,0:04:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,, The shipbuilding King Jihari is dealing with his own anxieties.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.03,0:04:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,, How by working tirelessly,\N he threw himself into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.51,0:04:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,, And this is where one of his biggest legacies really starts,\N isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.83,0:04:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,, In 55 AC,\N the laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.24,0:04:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,, Oh,\N absolutely. With his smaller council,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.68,0:04:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,, Sept and Barth,\N Grandmaster Benefer,\N Lord Albin Massey,\N and Queen Alessane was involved
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.56,0:04:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,, too. Right. They started trying to untangle this mess of contradictory laws
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.39,0:04:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,, across the seven kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.72,0:04:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,, Monumental is the word. Before Aegon's conquest,\N you had all these separate
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.72,0:04:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,, kingdoms,\N each with its own rules,\N its own customs,\N the sources say things
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.24,0:04:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,, like 97 kingdoms at one time,\N 132 at another.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.88,0:04:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,, And even after the conquest,\N it was still a patchwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.64,0:04:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,, Lord's pretty much ruled by whim based on conflicting precedence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:04:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,, So Jihari's wanted to change that,\N bring a single law to the realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.92,0:05:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,, Exactly. It wasn't just tidying up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.56,0:05:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,, It was about centralizing power,\N making justice more consistent,\N less arbitrary,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.72,0:05:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,, taking power away from individual Lord's whims and creating a,\N well,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.80,0:05:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,, unified legal framework that laid the groundwork for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.28,0:05:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,, Really,\N it absolutely did a fundamental shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.52,0:05:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,, But it wasn't all just dry legal work in 55 AC.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.56,0:05:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,, There were personal moments too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.16,0:05:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,, Queen Alessane was pregnant again,\N which was big news,\N though little princess
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.19,0:05:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,, Daenerys,\N who was four,\N apparently insisted she wanted a sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.04,0:05:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,, Oh,\N kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.96,0:05:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,, And Alessane was busy playing matchmaker too,\N wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.52,0:05:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,, For her wise women.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.88,0:05:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,, Yes,\N arranging really good marriages for them,\N integrating her household staff
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.00,0:05:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,, into the broader nobility,\N very savvy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.72,0:05:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,, Then there was the big turnie for the dragon pit completion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.60,0:05:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,, Sounds like quite the event.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.88,0:05:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,, 77 nights,\N a couple of deaths,\N unfortunately,\N but Sarah Luke
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.28,0:05:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,, more strong won the melee and Sir Simon Dondarian,\N crowned Princess
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.92,0:05:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,, Daenerys,\N queen of love and beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.60,0:05:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,, Sweet. Very.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.32,0:06:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,, But then Alessane decided to go to Dragonstone for the birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.36,0:06:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,, Yeah,\N the memory of losing Prince Aegon previously was still raw,\N right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.96,0:06:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,, She wanted quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.87,0:06:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,, Understandably.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.56,0:06:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,, So Jhery's went on a royal progress alone through the Western lands and pointedly
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.72,0:06:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,, skipped fair Isle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.72,0:06:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,, I can expect a Barthus Point,\N doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.40,0:06:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,, The unspoken threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.64,0:06:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,, Jhery's didn't need to shout like Riena,\N just snubbing Lord Farman sent a clear
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.28,0:06:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,, message,\N subtle,\N but effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.43,0:06:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,, Very.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.48,0:06:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,, And the retreat worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.12,0:06:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,, Alessane had a healthy baby boy on Dragonstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.48,0:06:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,, Prince Aiman,\N Lilac Eyes,\N white gold hair,\N sounds very Targaryen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.40,0:06:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,, Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.12,0:06:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,, And Jhery's put a dragon egg in his cradle,\N apparently at Alessane suggestion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.20,0:06:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,, A tradition continued.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.48,0:06:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,, And when they came back to King's landing,\N huge celebrations,\N the small
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.00,0:06:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,, folk apparently roared so loud you could hear to cross the Nero sea,\N bit of an
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.68,0:06:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,, exaggeration perhaps,\N but still shows the relief and joy,\N though.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.96,0:06:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,, Meanwhile,\N Queen Riena came back from Greenstone,\N found some comfort with her
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.75,0:06:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,, cousin,\N Larissa Valerian,\N unaware that Alice West Hill,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.00,0:07:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,, Alyssa Farman,\N her betrayer,\N was sailing the sun chaser right past the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,, stepstones nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.00,0:07:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,, So close,\N the irony.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.24,0:07:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,, So moving into 56 AC winter arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.80,0:07:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,, And the news from Essos about the search for area and Bolarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.52,0:07:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,, It's not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.32,0:07:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,, No,\N the search has failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.76,0:07:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,, Sir Willem the Was got ambushed by bandits in Andalos,\N not eaten by a monster
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.60,0:07:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,, and other sightings like that Wyvern and asked to pour just miss
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.96,0:07:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,, identifications of rumors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.52,0:07:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,, Hope was really fading.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.92,0:07:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,, It seemed like they might never know what happened and then everything
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.08,0:07:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,, changes dramatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.16,0:07:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,, 13th day,\N fourth moon of 56 AC,\N this massive horn blast over King's landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,, Valerian was back dread,\N right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.52,0:07:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,, Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.72,0:07:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,, People probably thought mega,\N the cruel and somehow returned exactly,\N but
