Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,, Oh my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.84,0:08:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,, And then when they put her in ice to try and cool her down,\N these things burst out
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.27,0:08:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,, of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.51,0:08:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,, He called them worms with faces,\N snakes with hands,\N twisting,\N slimy,\N unspeakable
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.07,0:08:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,, things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.71,0:08:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,, No,\N they rived and died in the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.00,0:08:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,, Barth's conclusion,\N Blarion must have taken her to Valeria.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.71,0:09:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,, Valeria itself,\N the doom still echoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.48,0:09:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,, Apparently the ancient,\N cursed source of dark magic,\N twisted creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.03,0:09:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,, Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.27,0:09:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,, And those things inside her products of that place,\N this sheer horror of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.79,0:09:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,, I can't even imagine.
