Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.75,0:09:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,, He issued that royal edict,\N no ship travels to Valeria or the smoking sea period on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.87,0:09:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,, pain of death,\N creating this permanent forbidden zone around the Targaryen
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.96,0:09:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,, homeland driven by this secret horror.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.63,0:09:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,, Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.56,0:09:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,, And Valeria,\N he became the first dragon house permanently in the dragon pit,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.88,0:09:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,, guarded day and night by the new dragon teepers to prevent anything like that ever
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.64,0:09:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,, happening again,\N a drastic measure born from terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.08,0:10:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,, Absolutely,\N a new era of vigilance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.24,0:10:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,, Can't pour queen reina,\N which she finally got the word of green stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.76,0:10:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,, Gary was already gone,\N burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.76,0:10:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,, She flew to the red keep,\N but all she received were ashes and bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.60,0:10:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,, Her line,\N it would seem that I am doomed to always come too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.28,0:10:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,, Just heartbreaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.20,0:10:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,, Yeah,\N and she wouldn't bury the ashes on dragon stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.48,0:10:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,, What she know,\N she told the king she hated dragon stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.08,0:10:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,, She wanted to fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.36,0:10:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,, So reina took the ashes up on dream fire and scattered them to the winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.12,0:10:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,, A final flight for area in a way,\N reina,\N then just retreated,\N refused
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.32,0:10:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,, dragon stone,\N green stone,\N even a seat on the small council.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.80,0:10:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,, Jehary's offered her and when Alice and gently suggested maybe remarrying,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.64,0:10:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,, having more children that famous line,\N I fed my last husband to my dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.12,0:10:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,, If you make me take another,\N I may eat him myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.12,0:10:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,, Oh,\N fear sort of finds just turned inward,\N isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.48,0:10:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,, It seems like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.24,0:10:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,, And she ended up where of all places,\N the cursed castle,\N specifically the widow's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.72,0:11:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,, tower,\N but strangely,\N she apparently formed a close friendship there with the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.60,0:11:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,, sickly meager towers,\N whose father was killed by meager,\N the cruel weird
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.36,0:11:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,, connections history makes,\N isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.43,0:11:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,, And she kept right in dream fire until she died in 73 AC aged 50,\N never went
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.24,0:11:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,, back to king's landing or dragon stone,\N just stayed away,\N a life marked by that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.44,0:11:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,, grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,, Okay,\N let's shift to something brighter,\N 57 AC,\N another royal birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.03,0:11:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,, Yes,\N Prince Balon,\N they called him the spring prince because the white
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.84,0:11:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,, ravens announcing spring arrived just before his birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.68,0:11:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,, Nice timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.56,0:11:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,, And he sounded like quite the character loud and lusty,\N a real contrast to his
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.56,0:11:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,, serious older brother,\N Aemon and their rather commanding sister Daenerys.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.39,0:11:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,, It didn't he get nicknamed Balon the Brave as a toddler?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.91,0:11:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,, For supposedly smacking Balarian on the snout.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.00,0:11:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,, Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.95,0:11:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,, Yes,\N that's the story,\N whether it's two or not,\N it's stuck,\N shows his spirit,\N I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.87,0:11:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,, But even here,\N there's a hint of tension right between J. Harry's and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.84,0:11:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,, Alessand about the succession.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.31,0:11:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,, There is subtly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.91,0:12:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,, J. Harry started talking about Aemon as his heir pretty much from birth,\N but
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.60,0:12:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,, Alessand kept pointing out that Daenerys was older.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.00,0:12:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,, She wanted Daenerys first in line.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.55,0:12:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,, Seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.63,0:12:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,, J. Harry's would say,\N oh,\N they'll rule together like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,, But Grandmaster Bennett for a noted,\N Alessand was never quite happy with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.60,0:12:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,, A rare point of disagreement for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.68,0:12:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,, Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.44,0:12:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,, Also in 57 AC,\N a big change on the small council.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.24,0:12:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,, Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.92,0:12:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,, Lord Miles Smallwood was out his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.40,0:12:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,, J. Harry's felt he was made to sit a horse,\N not a cushion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.80,0:12:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,, Fair enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.56,0:12:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,, And he was determined to a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.00,0:12:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,, Sept and Barth,\N despite the objections about his low birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.28,0:12:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,, And J. Harry's just shut down the complaints.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.32,0:12:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,, Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.72,0:12:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,, Famously said,\N a knight needs his sword,\N a horse needs shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.75,0:12:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,, And I need Barth,\N end of discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.51,0:12:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,, And Barth got straight to work,\N sent off to Brava as almost immediately within days,\N critical
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.56,0:12:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,, mission,\N deal with the sea lord about Alissa Farman and those stolen dragon eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.75,0:12:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,, That sounds like a tense negotiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.63,0:12:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,, Oh,\N you bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.72,0:12:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,, Vailed threats,\N flying back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.04,0:13:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,, Barth hinting at dragonfire,\N the sea lord mentioning,\N you know,\N skilled assassins who
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.87,0:13:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,, could target people in King's Landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.96,0:13:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,, High stakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.75,0:13:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,, So what was the outcome?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.80,0:13:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,, Did Barth get the eggs back?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.56,0:13:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,, No,\N he didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.75,0:13:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,, Which raises that question,\N was he outplayed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.67,0:13:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,, Where did he achieve something bigger?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.03,0:13:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,, What did he get?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.84,0:13:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,, He got the crown's massive debt to the iron bank,\N forgiven,\N essentially cut in half for the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.20,0:13:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,, cost of three stones as the sanguine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.20,0:13:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,, Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.72,0:13:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,, So no eggs,\N but massive debt relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.48,0:13:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,, Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.48,0:13:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,, The sea lord denied having the eggs,\N but offered gold instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.55,0:13:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,, Basically acknowledging J. Harry's leverage,\N but finding a different solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.15,0:13:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,, Barth realized financial freedom was maybe more valuable,\N long term than getting the eggs back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.80,0:13:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,, That's really smart diplomacy,\N practical over symbolic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.96,0:13:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,, Classic Barth and classic J. Harry's really pragmatic,\N focused on stability.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.16,0:13:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,, And that financial freedom had immediate effects back in King's Landing right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.24,0:13:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,, Huge effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.16,0:13:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,, Money that was going to the iron bank could now be used for improvements to sharies and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.96,0:13:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,, Rago draws his master of coin wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:14:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,, They'd already done some street widening,\N cobblestones,\N but now drains sewers and most
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.68,0:14:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,, famously the Queen's fountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.00,0:14:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,, Ah,\N Alessand's project.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.87,0:14:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,, How does that come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.68,0:14:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,, Well,\N Barth pointed out how awful the drinking water was in King's Landing,\N basically
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.16,0:14:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,, undrinkable for people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.63,0:14:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,, Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.16,0:14:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,, He proposed the zambitious scheme with wells and pipes,\N but J. Harry's and Rago
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.87,0:14:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,, draws were hesitant about the cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.12,0:14:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,, Understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.92,0:14:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,, So how did Alessand convince them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.72,0:14:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,, Simple,\N but brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.96,0:14:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,, At the next council meeting,\N she served them both a big tankard of the muddy river
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.08,0:14:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,, water they were discussing and just dared them to drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.00,0:14:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,, Did they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.60,0:14:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,, Nope,\N project approved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.68,0:14:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,, Brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.80,0:14:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,, And those fountains provided clean water for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.52,0:14:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,, Attangible improvement.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.64,0:14:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,, Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.44,0:14:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,, Built on financial cleverness and a Queen's determination.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.64,0:14:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,, Okay,\N let's move into 58 AC.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.84,0:14:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,, Big plans for a royal progress to the North.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.16,0:14:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,, Yeah,\N a really significant diplomatic move.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.88,0:14:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,, No Targaryen King had actually visited Winterfell since the conquest,\N but J.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.76,0:14:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,, Harry's got pulled away,\N didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.24,0:14:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,, He did.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.08,0:15:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,, There was a war between Pentos and Tyrosh messing up trade and he needed to go mediate
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.84,0:15:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,, a peace treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.80,0:15:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,, So the solution,\N Alessand goes north alone first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.15,0:15:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,, Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.84,0:15:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,, J.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.08,0:15:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,, Harry's would join her later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.32,0:15:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,, So Alessand heads off first up White Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.92,0:15:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,, How was her reception there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.15,0:15:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,, Pretty amazing,\N actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.75,0:15:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,, The small folk were awestruck,\N maybe a bit terrified seeing Silverwing land,\N first
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.87,0:15:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,, dragon for most of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.20,0:15:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.04,0:15:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,, And Lord the more mandrily laid on the hospitality lavish feasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.04,0:15:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,, Alessand immediately started doing her political matchmaking,\N arranging marriages
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.60,0:15:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,, for her ladies always work in the angles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.60,0:15:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,, And there was even a duel at the tourney they held between her sworn shield,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.12,0:15:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,, junk will dark and a wildling girl sounds memorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.80,0:15:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,, Definitely,\N but the most important thing she did there was convene her women's court.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.32,0:15:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,, Unheard of in the North,\N hundreds of women and girls came to Lord mandrily's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.56,0:15:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,, hall to speak directly to the queen,\N share their concerns,\N their grievances.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.68,0:15:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,, That's incredible setting a precedent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.27,0:15:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,, Yeah,\N absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.96,0:16:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,, And it really foreshadows what comes later shows her commitment to listening to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.68,0:16:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,, But the warm welcome didn't quite follow her to Winterfell did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.20,0:16:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,, No,\N Lord Elyric Stark was described as flinty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.28,0:16:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,, He and his sons met her,\N but he wasn't exactly rolling out the red carpet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.44,0:16:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,, What were his issues?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.72,0:16:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,, Seem like a few things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.80,0:16:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,, He apparently looked down on her southern clothes,\N didn't want Silverwing inside the castle walls,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.48,0:16:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,, grumbled that the king wasn't there,\N standard northern pride,\N maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.12,0:16:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,, Probably some of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.72,0:16:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,, He even apparently boasted about his own wife,\N Lady Mormart,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.03,0:16:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,, being unladylike,\N hunting wolves and sowing their skins into cloaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.56,0:16:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,, Okay,\N then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.48,0:16:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,, So a chilly reception.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.96,0:16:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,, How did Alice and handle it with what the sources call her stubborn charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.96,0:16:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,, Gradually,\N she won him over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.32,0:16:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,, She apparently managed to disprove the rumors that he had no humor or was stingy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.96,0:16:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,, He showed her giant bones,\N let her look through his library.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.84,0:16:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,, She bonded with his daughter,\N Alara.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.63,0:16:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,, So she bridged that North South gap impressive,\N took skill,\N but she did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.96,0:17:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,, And from Winterfell,\N she went even further north to the wall castle black.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.48,0:17:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,, Yeah,\N the night's watch were blown away,\N feasted her on mammoth meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.35,0:17:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,, Silverwing caused a stir again,\N but silverwing reacted strangely to the wall itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.35,0:17:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,, Very strangely,\N Alessanne wrote jihari's about it,\N said,\N Silverwing does not like this wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.72,0:17:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,, She tried three times to fly the dragon north beyond the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.67,0:17:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,, Yeah,\N Silverwing refused every time,\N veered back South.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.87,0:17:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,, Alessanne said the dragon had never refused her like that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.03,0:17:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,, That's interesting,\N unsettling almost.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.59,0:17:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,, It is,\N makes you wonder what the dragon sensed,\N but Alessanne's time there wasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.19,0:17:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,, just about weird dragon behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.35,0:17:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,, She saw the struggles of the night's watch,\N the wildlings,\N the harsh conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.15,0:17:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,, Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.15,0:17:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,, And that led directly to her first big queen's law,\N the new gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.87,0:17:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,, Right. She realized the land they had,\N Brandon's gift,\N wasn't enough to support them anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.35,0:17:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,, Correct. So she proposed giving them a whole new strip of land,\N South of the existing gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.11,0:18:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,, She convinced Lord Alaric Stark to agree to it,\N essentially doubling the watch's territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.96,0:18:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,, And she paid for a new castle,\N de-played herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.35,0:18:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,, She did. A really practical,\N lasting contribution based directly on what she saw and heard,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.68,0:18:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,, helping the watch sustain itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.35,0:18:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,, But her most transformative moment up north came next,\N didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.92,0:18:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,, When she visited Molstown.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.64,0:18:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,, Ah,\N yes. The village south of the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.96,0:18:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,, The Lord Commander was reluctant,\N but admitted she'd find,\N well,\N heartlets there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.84,0:18:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,, And she held another women's court.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.92,0:18:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,, Amongst those women.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.00,0:18:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,, Yes. And the story she heard there,\N they were the ones that would change the Seven Kingdoms forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.51,0:18:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,, She told the small council about one particular story back in King's Landing,\N right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.24,0:18:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,, The Blacksmith's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.24,0:18:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,, She did a horrific story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.40,0:18:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,, The girl marries her sweetheart and apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.31,0:18:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,, Vows barely spoken and the local Lord shows up to claim his right to the first night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.24,0:18:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,, Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.07,0:18:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,, Drags her off to flowers her brings her back the next morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.27,0:18:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,, The husband powerless against the Lord beats her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.51,0:19:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,, She ends up pregnant with the Lord's child,\N flees to Molstown,\N lives as a prostitute,\N utterly broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.40,0:19:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,, So awful. How did the council react?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,, It ignited a huge debate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.96,0:19:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,, Alasam was furious,\N fierce.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.24,0:19:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,, We are the sleeping dragons,\N she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.63,0:19:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,, These lords who love their first nights are dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.96,0:19:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,, Powerful words.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.39,0:19:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,, But J. Heres hesitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.79,0:19:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,, Initially,\N yeah,\N he pointed out how ancient the custom was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.35,0:19:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,, Lord Massie even tried to justify it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.83,0:19:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,, Claimed it was originally a blessing from first men heroes to sire strong kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.55,0:19:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,, Seriously,\N wow,\N how could a custom like that last so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.24,0:19:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,, Why was this the moment it got challenged?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.27,0:19:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,, That's the key question,\N isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.72,0:19:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,, It speaks volumes about ingrained traditions,\N however,\N barbaric.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.51,0:19:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,, But then septan bar stepped in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.24,0:19:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,, What did birth argue?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.20,0:19:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,, He hit it from all angles,\N said it was an offense against chivalry against the marriage
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.48,0:19:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,, vows sworn to the gods and crucially against the king's peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.60,0:19:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,, He basically called the first men who started it,\N savages who practiced blood
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.79,0:19:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,, sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.12,0:19:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,, We are not those men,\N he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.08,0:20:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,, He connected morality,\N religion and law precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.40,0:20:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,, He completely dismantled any shred of legitimacy the custom had.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.40,0:20:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,, It wasn't just about compassion anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.20,0:20:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,, It was about defining west to rocy society under j harries about the king's law
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.16,0:20:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,, and basic decency overriding ancient brutality and that swayed j harries completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.92,0:20:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,, The king apparently threw up his hands and said,\N I know when I am beaten very well,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.24,0:20:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,, let it be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.00,0:20:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,, It just like that abolished just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.24,0:20:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,, The right of the first night was abolished,\N taking a bride's maiden head became
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.64,0:20:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,, rape,\N whether you were a lord or a peasant,\N a truly revolutionary change.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.27,0:20:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,, Another queen's law amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.72,0:20:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,, So that brings us to the end of 58 AC,\N the 10th anniversary of j harries coronation,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.83,0:20:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,, a milestone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.87,0:20:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,, And the kingdom was in a very different state than when he took the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.00,0:20:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,, He's 24 now,\N not a boy king anymore,\N described as handsome,\N wise,\N golden beard,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.11,0:20:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,, the image of the conciliator.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.07,0:20:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,, And Alessand is good queen,\N Alessand truly beloved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.72,0:21:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,, They had been through so much grief that horror with area political challenges,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.24,0:21:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,, but they seem stronger and the real peaceful,\N prosperous,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.72,0:21:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,, more so than anyone could remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.40,0:21:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,, The queen's laws had made real differences.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.44,0:21:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,, It's an undeniable record of achievement by this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.68,0:21:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,, Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.48,0:21:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,, Peace,\N prosperity,\N genuine social reform,\N improving lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.96,0:21:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,, They had a big celebration right,\N another turning king's landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,, Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.27,0:21:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,, So rhyme red wine was the champion this time,\N crowned Alessand queen of love and beauty,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.31,0:21:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,, huge cheers from the commons.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.88,0:21:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,, Lords came from all over for the feast,\N a real moment of unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.20,0:21:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,, It seemed like it though there was that bittersweet moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.48,0:21:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,, Alessand apparently wept when she saw Septa Ralea,\N her daughter,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.31,0:21:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,, because Ralea looked so much like area would have grown older,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.03,0:21:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,, a reminder of the loss amidst the joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.24,0:21:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,, Uh,\N yeah,\N that shadow still lingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.24,0:21:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,, But overall,\N the sources painted as a golden time,\N don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.11,0:21:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,, A golden autumn,\N they call it peace,\N plenty,\N reconciliation,\N a high point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.44,0:21:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,, But there's always a but in these stories,\N isn't there always the final line
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.40,0:22:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,, from the sources for this period is ominous,\N but winter was coming,\N chilling.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.88,0:22:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,, So looking back at these few years,\N what a complex picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.24,0:22:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,, It really is an intricate tapestry like you said,\N incredible progress,\N stability for the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.04,0:22:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,, realm yet marked so deeply by these personal tragedies,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.16,0:22:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,, these unsettling secrets known only to a few that duality seems key.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.72,0:22:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,, The public triumphs built on or at least alongside private horrors.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.20,0:22:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,, It certainly seems that way for this period,\N which leaves us and you listening
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.55,0:22:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,, with maybe a final thought to chew on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.72,0:22:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,, How often is history like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.75,0:22:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,, How many foundational moments golden ages even are built not just on the victories we
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.03,0:22:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,, celebrate,\N but also on unspoken horrors,\N on secrets kept by a powerful few?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.03,0:22:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,, What hitting truths might still be lurking just beneath the surface,\N even in times
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.59,0:22:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,, that look peaceful,\N just waiting for someone to do a deep dive and bring them out.
